# ─── Test Environment Variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT IS THIS FILE?
# This file contains environment variables used by the test suite. It is loaded
# automatically by Vitest via `tests/setup.ts`.
#
# HOW TO USE:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.test .env.test.local
# 2. Fill in DATABASE_URL_TEST with a real test database URL (see below)
# 3. .env.test.local is gitignored, so your credentials stay local
#
# ─── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# For a test database, create a separate branch in Neon:
#   1. Go to Neon console → your project → Branches
#   2. Click "New branch" → name it "test"
#   3. Copy the connection string and paste it below
#
# Alternatively, install PostgreSQL locally: brew install postgresql
# Then: createdb latin_lite_test
#
DATABASE_URL_TEST="postgresql://neondb_owner:npg_DSIvpgWP9Jm5@ep-super-king-ah17byw3-pooler.c-3.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require&channel_binding=require" 

